    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Truth on Guatemala</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Julie Schifeling letter comments on August 20 editorial demanding accountability for thousands of missing children abducted during Guatemala's 36-year civil war</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Guatemala's Missing Children'' (editorial, Aug. 20):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Guatemala's Missing Children'' (editorial, Aug. 20):</p>
        <p>Your editorial prompts me to ask why Congress has not passed the Human Rights Information Act, which would mandate an immediate review of all United States documents pertaining to human rights violations in Honduras and Guatemala and set deadlines for declassification.</p>
        <p>The declassification procedure  would help countless families overseas discover what happened to their loved ones while fully protecting national security interests of the United States.</p>
        <p>It is time for the United States to help these families learn the truth.</p>
        <p>JULIE SCHIFELING  Metamora, Ill., Aug. 23, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is Illinois legislative coordinator, Amnesty International U.S.A.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
